In the teabag rocket we showed that if you
light a teabag on fire from the top it will

00:05:15.099 --> 00:05:20.639
actually take off into the air. That happens
because as the teabag is burning all the air

00:05:20.639 --> 00:05:26.080
inside it heats up and so it expands so it
gets less dense and it's pushed up by all

00:05:26.080 --> 00:05:32.240
the cooler air around it. You know, sometimes
people talk about how hot air rises. I mean,

00:05:32.240 --> 00:05:37.120
that is what hot air does, but only because
the cooler air around it is pushing it up.

00:05:37.120 --> 00:05:41.219
In essence it's like a buoyant force because
the hot air is now less dense than the cooler

00:05:41.219 --> 00:05:46.020
air around it. So, when the teabag burns right
down to the bottom the remaining ash is so

00:05:46.020 --> 00:05:53.930
light that it gets swept up in that convection
current, and you get a teabag rocket. So do

